About the Series:
The series is primarily set in Yorkshire, and follows the work of two detectives that are 
thrown together as partners.
Some episodes in this series are divided on on the DVDs into part 1 and part 2 but I have encoded
these together to give the original episode as broadcast, so don't be supprised at credits
at 50 minutes in, as the whole episode is there and all episodes are approx 100 minutes. 

Episode 1 "The Cave Woman"
A rescue mission to save several trapped cavers reveals the remains of Lyn Baron, the ex-wife 
of the current chief constable, who disappeared in 1985 on the way to see her children.

Episode 2 "Fallen Angel"
When popular jockey Sammy Hogarth dies from a high dose of warfarin, Dalziel and Pascoe 
are forced to investigate the dark side of horse racing.

Episode 3 "Demons on Our Shoulders"
Innocent housewife Jean Hamilton is blasted to death with a shotgun in her bedroom on 
Halloween, her husband, Guy is quickly identified as the prime suspect.

Episode 4 "Project Aphrodite"
Researcher Declan Roach is found dead at the local university, having been poisoned 
with liquid nitrogen in the laboratory clean room.

Episode 5 "Under Dark Stars"
In their final case, Dalziel and Pascoe are faced with the grief of two families 
whose sons were murdered by convicted paedophile Michael Wheeler, only for him 
to be acquitted and walk free from court.
